items.title: Lyft closes 28% higher after issuing buyback and posting bookings growth
items.description: Lyft shares popped 28% after the ride-sharing company upped its share buyback plan and posted better-than-expected gross bookings.

items.title: Texas Roadhouse's momentum in April blunts inflation risk nipping at its heels
items.description: Early signs of a stronger second quarter were giving investors hope.

items.title: Coinbase shares fall after first-quarter revenue misses Wall Street estimates
items.description: Earlier Thursday, Coinbase announced plans to buy Dubai-based Deribit, in an attempt to broaden its international business.

items.title: Krispy Kreme stock plunges after doughnut chain pauses McDonald's rollout, pulls outlook
items.description: Krispy Kreme is pausing its nationwide rollout with McDonald's to focus on profitability.

items.title: AppLovin shares pop on earnings beat as it announces sale of mobile gaming business
items.description: AppLovin shares soared in extended trading after the company beat first-quarter expectations and announced the sale of its mobile gaming business.
